- Scalable, maintainable, extensible, readable

OOP (Object oriented programming)
Real world         <------>       Software

1. Actors          <------>       Data (value) -- Objects
- Student
- Professor                       `class Student` --- 1 to n Objects can be created. Name of the class gives
                                   data type to the object.
                                   Built in classes -- str,  int, float, bool
- Book
- Author
....

2. Characteristics of    <-------> Attributes on the object
the actors

3. Actions that we do on the actors <--------> Methods called on the object



General success flow
Python interpreter -> play_input -> '45' -> int('45') -> 45 -> odd -> Program ends

Error flow 1
Python interpreter -> play_input -> 'good morning' -> int('good morning')
  -> raises (throws) a ValueError -> play_input -> rethrow - reraise ValueError -> Python interpreter

Error flow 2
Python interpreter -> play_input -> 'good morning' -> int('good morning')
  -> raises (throws) a ValueError -> play_input -> handle the error (ValueError) -> Program ends